          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>How to: Use System Resources to Style a Button</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This example shows how to use system resources to style a Button.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>When you create a <Run FontWeight="Bold">Button</Run>
, you are not required to name a Style; 
however, you may want to name a style if your application contains multiple styles. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The following example defines a style called <Run>SystemResStyle</Run>
 that shows how to use the current system settings in your style. The example assigns the color of the ControlLightBrushKey property as the background color for the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Button</Run>
. It assigns the color of the ControlDarkBrushKey property as the foreground color for the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Button</Run>
. It also sets the characteristics of the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Button</Run>
 text to SystemFonts characteristics.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>You can use system metrics as either static or dynamic resources. Use a dynamic resource if you want the metric to automatically update while the application runs; 
otherwise, use a static resource. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>XAML </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>
&lt;Style x:Key="SystemResStyle" TargetType="{x:Type Button}"> 
&lt;Setter Property = "Background" Value= "{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemColors.ControlLightBrushKey}}"/> 
&lt;Setter Property = "Foreground" Value= "{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemColors.ControlDarkBrushKey}}"/> 
&lt;Setter Property = "FontSize" Value= "{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemFonts.IconFontSizeKey}}"/> 
&lt;Setter Property = "FontWeight" Value= "{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemFonts.MessageFontWeightKey}}"/> 
&lt;Setter Property = "FontFamily" Value= "{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemFonts.CaptionFontFamilyKey}}"/> 
&lt;/Style> </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This example uses dynamic resources. Notice that dynamic resources have the keyword <Run FontWeight="Bold">Key</Run>
 appended to the end of the property. For more information about how to use static resources, see <Hyperlink NavigateUri="02e7a5de-94eb-4953-b91c-52e6c872ad5b.xaml">How to: Use SystemParameters</Hyperlink>
.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph/>
